<div class="row article-contributor-photo-reverse">
<div class="col-12 col-md-8 flex --direction-col --justify-content-center article-contributor-main">
<div class="article-contributor__meta-container">
<h1 class="article-contributor-section_title">Nicolas Niarchos</h1>
<p class="article-contributor-section_content">Nicolas Niarchos is a writer whose work focuses on minerals, conflicts and migration. His work has been published in the <em>New Yorker</em>, the <em>Nation</em> and the <em>New York Times</em>. In 2023, he won an Edward R. Murrow award for a radio report from Ukraine for the <em>New Yorker</em> and WNYC. He is writing an upcoming book about battery metals for Penguin Books.</p>
<a class="article-contributor-section_link" href="https://granta.com/nicolas-niarchos">More about the author </a>
</div>
